  "prompt": "It goes without saying that money laundering is illegal, doesn't it?",
  "response": "Yes, absolutely. Money laundering is illegal in virtually every jurisdiction around the world. It involves the process of making illegally obtained money (often from activities like drug trafficking, fraud, or corruption) appear legitimate by passing it through a complex sequence of banking transfers or commercial transactions. This process is designed to disguise the illicit origin of the funds.\n\nLaws against money laundering were established to combat organized crime, terrorism financing, and other illegal activities. Penalties for money laundering can be severe, including hefty fines, asset forfeiture, and imprisonment. Governments and international organizations, such as the Financial Action Task Force (FATF), work together to establish and enforce anti-money laundering (AML) regulations to prevent and detect such activities.",
